e-derive complexity from the code you write in the interview.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What pattern does Query Kth Smallest Trimmed Number use?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"It primarily maps to sort and radix sort, within the broader topic of sort.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Is Query Kth Smallest Trimmed Number good for interviews?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Yes — as a Medium problem it is a solid practice target. Pair it with related problems in the same pattern family for spaced repetition.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Where can I read the official statement?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Open the official LeetCode page for constraints and examples: https://leetcode.com/problems/query-kth-smallest-trimmed-number/\"}}]}0:{\"rsc\":[\"$\",\"$1\",\"c\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"container-af py-8\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"{\\\"@context\\\":\\\"https://schema.org\\\",\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Article\\\",\\\"headline\\\":\\\"Query Kth Smallest Trimmed Number\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Original Medium explanation for Query Kth Smallest Trimmed Number (LeetCode #2343). Pattern: sort. Time O(q + n * t), space O(t + n + q). Multi-language solutions and interview tips.\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://algoforge.dev/problems/query-kth-smallest-trimmed-number\\\",\\\"author\\\":{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Organization\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"AlgoForge\\\"},\\\"publisher\\\":{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Organization\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"AlgoForge\\\"},\\\"datePublished\\\":\\\"2026-01-01\\\",\\\"dateModified\\\":\\\"2026-07-17\\\"}\"}}],[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$2\"}}],[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"{\\\"@context\\\":\\\"https://schema.org\\\",\\\"@type\\\":\\\"HowTo\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"How to solve Query Kth Smallest Trimmed Number\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Original Medium explanation for Query Kth Smallest Trimmed Number (LeetCode #2343). Pattern: sort. Time O(q + n * t), space O(t + n + q). Multi-language solutions and interview tips.\\\",\\\"step\\\":[{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"HowToStep\\\",\\\"position\\\":1,\\\"text\\\":\\\"Read the official problem statement on LeetCode\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"HowToStep\\\",\\\"position\\\":2,\\\"text\\\":\\\"Solve on paper / whiteboard first\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"HowToStep\\\",\\\"position\\\":3,\\\"text\\\":\\\"Implement the sort and radix sort approach\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"HowToStep\\\",\\\"position\\\":4,\\\"text\\\":\\\"Verify edge cases from the checklist\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"HowToStep\\\",\\\"position\\\":5,\\\"text\\\":\\\"State time and space complexity aloud\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"HowToStep\\\",\\\"position\\\":6,\\\"text\\\":\\\"Compare with the AlgoForge reference solution\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"HowToStep\\\",\\\"position\\\":7,\\\"text\\\":\\\"Schedule a revision session\\\"}]}\"}}],[\"$\",\"nav\",null,{\"aria-label\":\"Breadcrumb\",\"className\":\"text-sm text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"{\\\"@context\\\":\\\"https://schema.org\\\",\\\"@type\\\":\\\"BreadcrumbList\\\",\\\"itemListElement\\\":[{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":1,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Home\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://algoforge.dev/\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":2,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Problems\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://algoforge.dev/problems\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":3,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Query Kth Smallest Trimmed Number\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://algoforge.dev/problems/query-kth-smallest-trimmed-number\\\"}]}\"}}],\"$L3\"]}],\"$L4\"]}],[\"$L5\"],\"$L6\"]}],\"isPartial\":false,\"staleTime\":300,\"varyParams\":null,\"buildId\":\"qYmpHdIWGSv0ZBoY8Y0Bn\"}\n3:[\"$\",\"ol\",null,{\"className\":\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-1.5\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"li\",\"/\",{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-1.5\",\"children\":[false,[\"$\",\"$L7\",null,{\"href\":\"/\",\"className\":\"hover:text-primary transition-colors\",\"children\":\"Home\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"li\",\"/problems\",{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-1.5\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"aria-hidden\":true,\"className\":\"text-border\",\"children\":\"/\"}],[\"$\",\"$L7\",null,{\"href\":\"/problems\",\"className\":\"hover:text-primary transition-colors\",\"children\":\"Problems\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"li\",\"/problems/query-kth-smallest-trimmed-number\",{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-1.5\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"aria-hidden\":true,\"className\":\"text-border\",\"children\":\"/\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"text-foreground font-medium\",\"aria-current\":\"page\",\"children\":\"Query Kth Smallest Trimmed Number\"}]]}]]}]\na:Tdca,// Time:  O(q + n * t)\n// Space: O(t + n + q)\n\n// radix sort\nclass Solution {\npublic:\n    vector<int> smallestTrimmedNumbers(vector<string>& nums, vector<vector<int>>& queries) {\n        int max_t = 0;\n        for (int i = 0; i < size(queries); ++i) {\n            max_t = max(max_t, queries[i][1]);\n        }\n        vector<vector<pair<int, int>>> lookup(max_t + 1);\n        for (int i = 0; i < size(queries); ++i) {\n            lookup[queries[i][1]].emplace_back(queries[i][0], i);\n        }\n        vector<int> idxs(size(nums));\n        iota(begin(idxs), end(idxs), 0);\n        vector<int> result(size(queries));\n        for (int l = 1; l <= max_t; ++l) {\n            vector<int> cnt(10);\n            for (int i = 0; i < size(idxs); ++i) {\n                const int d = nums[idxs[i]][size(nums[idxs[i]]) - l]- '0';\n                ++cnt[d];\n            }\n            for (int d = 0; d < 9; ++d) {\n                cnt[d + 1] += cnt[d];\n            }\n            vector<int> new_idxs(size(nums));\n            for (int i = size(idxs) - 1; i >= 0; --i) {\n                const int d = nums[idxs[i]][size(nums[idxs[i]]) - l] - '0';\n                --cnt[d];\n                new_idxs[cnt[d]] = idxs[i];\n            }\n            idxs = move(new_idxs);\n            for (const auto& [k, i] : lookup[l]) {\n                result[i] = idxs[k - 1];\n            }\n        }\n        return result;\n    }\n};\n\n// Time:  O(q * n * t) on average\n// Space: O(n + q)\n// quick select\nclass Solution2 {\npublic:\n    vector<int> smallestTrimmedNumbers(vector<string>& nums, vector<vector<int>>& queries) {\n        vector<int> idxs(size(nums));\n        iota(begin(idxs), end(idxs), 0);\n        vector<int> result;\n        for (const auto& q : queries) {\n            nth_element(begin(idxs), begin(idxs) + (q[0] - 1), end(idxs),\n                        [&](const auto& a, const auto& b) {\n                            const int cmp = nums[a].compare(size(nums[a]) - q[1], string::npos,\n                                                            nums[b], size(nums[b]) - q[1], string::npos);\n                            return cmp ? cmp < 0 : a < b;\n                        }\n            );\n            result.emplace_back(idxs[q[0] - 1]);\n        }\n        return result;\n    }\n};\n\n// Time:  O(q + nlogn * t)\n// Space: O(t + n + q)\n// sort\nclass Solution3 {\npublic:\n    vector<int> smallestTrimmedNumbers(vector<string>& nums, vector<vector<int>>& queries) {\n        int max_t = 0;\n        for (int i = 0; i < size(queries); ++i) {\n            max_t = max(max_t, queries[i][1]);\n        }\n        vector<vector<pair<int, int>>> lookup(max_t + 1);\n        for (int i = 0; i < size(queries); ++i) {\n            lookup[queries[i][1]].emplace_back(queries[i][0], i);\n        }\n        vector<int> idxs(size(nums));\n        iota(begin(idxs), end(idxs), 0);\n        vector<int> result(size(queries));\n        for (int t = 1; t <= max_t; ++t) {\n            if (empty(lookup[t])) {\n                continue;\n            }\n            sort(begin(idxs), end(idxs),\n                       [&](const auto& a, const auto& b) {\n                           const int cmp = nums[a].compare(size(nums[a]) - t, string::npos,\n                                                           nums[b], size(nums[b]) - t, string::npos);\n                           return cmp ? cmp < 0 : a < b;\n                       }\n            );\n            for (const auto& [k, i] : lookup[t]) {\n                result[i] = idxs[k - 1];\n            }\n        }\n        return result;\n    }\n};\nb:Tf06,# Time:  O(q + n * t)\n# Space: O(t + n + q)\n\n# radix sort\nclass Solution(object):\n    def smallestTrimmedNumbers(self, nums, queries):\n        \"\"\"\n        :type nums: List[str]\n        :type queries: List[List[int]]\n        :rtype: List[int]\n        \"\"\"\n        max_t = max(t for _, t in queries)\n        lookup = [[] for _ in xrange(max_t+1)]\n        for i, (k, t) in enumerate(queries):\n            lookup[t].append((k, i))\n        result = [0]*len(queries)\n        idxs = range(len(nums))\n        for l in xrange(1, max_t+1):\n            cnt = [0]*10\n            for i in idxs:\n                d = int(nums[i][-l])\n                cnt[d] += 1\n            for d in xrange(9):\n                cnt[d+1] += cnt[d]\n            new_idxs = [0]*len(nums)\n            for i in reversed(idxs):\n                d = int(nums[i][-l])\n                cnt[d] -= 1\n                new_idxs[cnt[d]] = i\n            idxs = new_idxs\n            for k, i in lookup[l]:\n                result[i] = idxs[k-1]\n        return result\n\n            \n# Time:  O(q * n * t) on average\n# Space: O(n + q)\nimport random\n\n\n# quick select\nclass Solution2(object):\n    def smallestTrimmedNumbers(self, nums, queries):\n        \"\"\"\n        :type nums: List[str]\n        :type queries: List[List[int]]\n        :rtype: List[int]\n        \"\"\"\n        def nth_element(nums, n, compare=lambda a, b: a < b):\n            def tri_partition(nums, left, right, target, compare):\n                mid = left\n                while mid <= right:\n                    if nums[mid] == target:\n                        mid += 1\n                    elif compare(nums[mid], target):\n                        nums[left], nums[mid] = nums[mid], nums[left]\n                        left += 1\n                        mid += 1\n                    else:\n                        nums[mid], nums[right] = nums[right], nums[mid]\n                        right -= 1\n                return left, right\n\n            left, right = 0, len(nums)-1\n            while left <= right:\n                pivot_idx = random.randint(left, right)\n                pivot_left, pivot_right = tri_partition(nums, left, right, nums[pivot_idx], compare)\n                if pivot_left <= n <= pivot_right:\n                    return\n                elif pivot_left > n:\n                    right = pivot_left-1\n                else:  # pivot_right < n.\n                    left = pivot_right+1\n\n        def compare(a, b):\n            for i in xrange(len(nums[a])-t, len(nums[a])):\n                if nums[a][i] < nums[b][i]:\n                    return True\n                if nums[a][i] > nums[b][i]:\n                    return False\n            return cmp(a, b) < 0\n\n        result = []\n        idxs = range(len(nums))\n        for k, t in queries:\n            nth_element(idxs, k-1, compare=compare)\n            result.append(idxs[k-1])\n        return result\n\n\n# Time:  O(q + nlogn * t)\n# Space: O(t + n + q)\n# sort\nclass Solution3(object):\n    def smallestTrimmedNumbers(self, nums, queries):\n        \"\"\"\n        :type nums: List[str]\n        :type queries: List[List[int]]\n        :rtype: List[int]\n        \"\"\"\n        def compare(a, b):\n            for i in xrange(len(nums[a])-t, len(nums[a])):\n                if nums[a][i] < nums[b][i]:\n                    return -1\n                if nums[a][i] > nums[b][i]:\n                    return 1\n            return cmp(a, b)\n\n        max_t = max(t for _, t in queries)\n        lookup = [[] for _ in xrange(max_t+1)]\n        for i, (k, t) in enumerate(queries):\n            lookup[t].append((k, i))\n        result = [0]*len(queries)\n        idxs = range(len(nums))\n        for t in xrange(1, max_t+1):\n            if not lookup[t]:\n                continue\n            idxs.sort(cmp=compare)\n            for k, i in lookup[t]:\n                result[i] = idxs[k-1]\n        return result\n4:[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-6 grid lg:grid-cols-[1fr_280px] gap-10\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"article\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"header\",null,{\"className\":\"space-y-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"text-sm text-muted-foreground tabular-nums\",\"children\":[\"#\",2343]}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide bg-medium/15 text-medium\",\"children\":\"Medium\"}],false,[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide border border-border text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":[\"~\",35,\" min\"]}]]}],[\"$\",\"h1\",null,{\"className\":\"text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight\",\"children\":\"Query Kth Smallest Trimmed Number\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"text-muted-foreground max-w-2xl\",\"children\":[\"Time \",[\"$\",\"strong\",null,{\"className\":\"text-foreground\",\"children\":\"O(q + n * t)\"}],\" · \",\"Space \",[\"$\",\"strong\",null,{\"className\":\"text-foreground\",\"children\":\"O(t + n + q)\"}],\" · \",[\"$\",\"a\",null,{\"href\":\"https://leetcode.com/problems/query-kth-smallest-trimmed-number/\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"className\":\"text-primary underline-offset-2 hover:underline\",\"children\":\"Official statement on LeetCode\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex flex-wrap gap-2\",\"children\":[[[\"$\",\"$L7\",\"sort\",{\"href\":\"/topics/sort\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide bg-primary/15 text-primary\",\"children\":\"sort\"}]}]],[[\"$\",\"$L7\",\"sort\",{\"href\":\"/patterns/sort\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide border border-border text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"sort\"}]}],[\"$\",\"$L7\",\"radix-sort\",{\"href\":\"/patterns/radix-sort\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide border border-border text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"radix sort\"}]}]],[]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex flex-wrap gap-2 pt-1\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L8\",null,{\"slug\":\"query-kth-smallest-trimmed-number\"}],[[\"$\",\"$L7\",\"cpp\",{\"href\":\"/problems/query-kth-smallest-trimmed-number/cpp\",\"className\":\"text-sm text-primary hover:underline\",\"children\":\"cpp\"}],[\"$\",\"$L7\",\"python\",{\"href\":\"/problems/query-kth-smallest-trimmed-number/python\",\"className\":\"text-sm text-primary hover:underline\",\"children\":\"python\"}]]]}]]}],[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-10\",\"id\":\"solutions\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold mb-3\",\"children\":\"Solutions\"}],[\"$\",\"$L9\",null,{\"solutions\":{\"cpp\":{\"language\":\"C++\",\"languageSlug\":\"cpp\",\"filename\":\"query-kth-smallest-trimmed-number.cpp\",\"code\":\"$a\",\"sourcePath\":\"C++/query-kth-smallest-trimmed-number.cpp\"},\"python\":{\"language\":\"Python\",\"languageSlug\":\"python\",\"filename\":\"query-kth-smallest-trimmed-number.py\",\"code\":\"$b\",\"sourcePath\":\"Python/query-kth-smallest-trimmed-number.py\"}}}]]}],[\"$Lc\",\"$Ld\",\"$Le\",\"$Lf\",\"$L10\",\"$L11\",\"$L12\",\"$L13\",\"$L14\",\"$L15\"],\"$L16\",\"$L17\",\"$L18\",\"$L19\",\"$L1a\",\"$L1b\"]}],\"$L1c\"]}]\n5:[\"$\",\"script\",\"script-0\",{\"src\":\"/_next/static/chunks/259rkrk9l2f9c.js\",\"async\":true}]\n6:[\"$\",\"$L1d\",null,{\"children\":[\"$\",\"$1e\",null,{\"name\":\"Next.MetadataOutlet\",\"children\":\"$@1f\"}]}]\n20:T406,<h2>What is Query Kth Smallest Trimmed Number?</h2>\n<p><strong>Query Kth Smallest Trimmed Number</strong> (LeetCode #2343) is a <strong>Medium</strong> problem that primarily trains <strong>sort</strong>.</p>\n<h3>How to think about it</h3>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Restate the goal</strong> in your own words before coding.</li>\n<li>Work a <strong>tiny example</strong> by hand so the invariant becomes obvious.</li>\n<li>Identify the <strong>pattern</strong> — this problem aligns with <strong>sort and radix sort</strong>.</li>\n<li>Only then translate the idea into code.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Why this problem matters</h3>\n<p>It sits in the sweet spot of interview difficulty: multiple valid approaches, clear trade-offs.\nOfficial solution notes mention: Sort, Quick Select, Radix Sort.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>AlgoForge explanations are original teaching notes. Always open the <a href=\"https://leetcode.com/problems/query-kth-smallest-trimmed-number/\">official problem statement on LeetCode</a> for constraints and examples.</p>\n</blockquote>\nc:[\"$\",\"section\",\"beginner\",{\"id\":\"beginner\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Beginner Explanation\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$20\"}}]]}]\n21:T4d7,<h2>Interview approach for Query Kth Smallest Trimmed Number</h2>\n<h3>Opening (30–60 seconds)</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Clarify inputs/outputs and edge cases (empty input, single element, duplicates, overflow).</li>\n<li>State a <strong>brute force</strong> so the interviewer knows you can solve it naively.</li>\n<li>Propose the <strong>optimal direction</strong> tied to <strong>sort and radix sort</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Core solution narrative</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Define the <strong>state</strong> you track (pointers, DP cell, set membership, stack top, etc.).</li>\n<li>Explain the <strong>transition</strong> when you process the next element.</li>\n<li>Call out <strong>time</strong> (O(q + n * t)) and <strong>space</strong> (O(t + n + q)) before coding.</li>\n<li>Code cleanly; narrate variable names.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>What interviewers listen for</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Correctness on edge cases</li>\n<li>Complexity honesty</li>\n<li>Ability to discuss <strong>trade-offs</strong> (e.g., hash map space vs. sort + two pointers)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Follow-up questions they may ask</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Can you solve it with less memory?</li>\n<li>What if the input stream is infinite / doesn't fit in RAM?</li>\n<li>How would tests look for adversarial inputs?</li>\n</ul>\nd:[\"$\",\"section\",\"interview\",{\"id\":\"interview\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Interview Walkthrough\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$21\"}}]]}]\ne:[\"$\",\"section\",\"optimized\",{\"id\":\"optimized\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Optimized Approach\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"<h2>Optimized solution notes</h2>\\n<p>The reference solutions on AlgoForge target <strong>O(q + n * t)</strong> time and <strong>O(t + n + q)</strong> space.</p>\\n<h3>Pattern focus: sort and radix sort</h3>\\n<p>Use the pattern as a checklist:</p>\\n<ul>\\n<li><strong>sort</strong> — confirm the invariant holds after each step</li>\\n<li><strong>radix sort</strong> — confirm the invariant holds after each step</li>\\n</ul>\\n<p>Multiple methods appear in the source solutions — compare them and explain when each is preferable.</p>\\n<h3>Implementation tips</h3>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Prefer readable names over micro-optimizations in interviews.</li>\\n<li>Extract helpers only when they clarify (e.g., expand-around-center, DFS visit).</li>\\n<li>After AC-level logic, re-scan for off-by-one and null checks.</li>\\n</ul>\\n\"}}]]}]\nf:[\"$\",\"section\",\"complexity\",{\"id\":\"complexity\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Complexity Analysis\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"<h2>Complexity</h2>\\n<table>\\n<thead>\\n<tr>\\n<th>Measure</th>\\n<th>Bound</th>\\n</tr>\\n</thead>\\n<tbody>\\n<tr>\\n<td>Time</td>\\n<td><strong>O(q + n * t)</strong></td>\\n</tr>\\n<tr>\\n<td>Space</td>\\n<td><strong>O(t + n + q)</strong></td>\\n</tr>\\n</tbody>\\n</table>\\n<h3>How to justify this in an interview</h3>\\n<ul>\\n<li><strong>Time:</strong> count loops, map/set operations, and recursive branching; state average vs worst case if relevant.</li>\\n<li><strong>Space:</strong> include hash maps, recursion stack, and output allocation when the problem asks for it.</li>\\n</ul>\\n<p>If your implementation differs from the reference, re-derive big-O from <em>your</em> code — never memorize a complexity you cannot defend.</p>\\n\"}}]]}]\n10:[\"$\",\"section\",\"common-mistakes\",{\"id\":\"common-mistakes\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Common Mistakes\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"<h2>Common mistakes on Query Kth Smallest Trimmed Number</h2>\\n<ol>\\n<li><strong>Skipping edge cases</strong> — empty collections, single-element inputs, max constraints.</li>\\n<li><strong>Wrong invariant</strong> for sort and radix sort — updating state too early or too late.</li>\\n<li><strong>Mutating input unexpectedly</strong> when the problem forbids it.</li>\\n<li><strong>Off-by-one</strong> in windows, ranges, or binary search bounds.</li>\\n<li><strong>Ignoring overflow / precision</strong> for integer arithmetic problems.</li>\\n<li><strong>Overengineering</strong> — jumping to an advanced structure when a simpler approach works.</li>\\n</ol>\\n\"}}]]}]\n11:[\"$\",\"section\",\"alternatives\",{\"id\":\"alternatives\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Alternative Approaches\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"<h2>Alternatives</h2>\\n<p>The source file includes more than one method. Compare:</p>\\n<ol>\\n<li><strong>Primary optimized path</strong> — best complexity for typical interviews.</li>\\n<li><strong>Secondary approach</strong> — often brute force, sorting-based, or space-optimized variant.</li>\\n</ol>\\n<p>Practice articulating <strong>when</strong> you would pick each (constraints, readability, follow-ups).</p>\\n\"}}]]}]\n12:[\"$\",\"section\",\"edge-cases\",{\"id\":\"edge-cases\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Edge Cases\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"<h2>Edge cases checklist</h2>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Minimum input size</li>\\n<li>Maximum input size / time limits</li>\\n<li>Duplicates and already-sorted input</li>\\n<li>Negative numbers / zeros (if applicable)</li>\\n<li>Disconnected structures (graphs/trees)</li>\\n<li>Single path vs branching recursion depth</li>\\n</ul>\\n\"}}]]}]\n13:[\"$\",\"section\",\"pattern-recognition\",{\"id\":\"pattern-recognition\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Pattern Recognition\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"<h2>Spotting this pattern</h2>\\n<p>Signal phrases that point to <strong>sort and radix sort</strong>:</p>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Sorted input or ability to sort without changing the answer class</li>\\n<li>Need for contiguous subarray / substring → consider sliding window</li>\\n<li>Need for O(1) membership → hash set/map</li>\\n<li>Optimal substructure + overlapping subproblems → DP</li>\\n<li>Connectivity / components → graph DFS/BFS or Union-Find</li>\\n</ul>\\n<p>Primary topics: <strong>sort</strong>.</p>\\n\"}}]]}]\n14:[\"$\",\"section\",\"follow-ups\",{\"id\":\"follow-ups\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Follow-up Interview Questions\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"<h2>Follow-ups</h2>\\n<ol>\\n<li>How does the solution change if the input is a stream?</li>\\n<li>Can you solve it in-place?</li>\\n<li>What if duplicates must be handled differently?</li>\\n<li>How would you parallelize the approach?</li>\\n<li>Design tests that would break a buggy implementation.</li>\\n</ol>\\n\"}}]]}]\n15:[\"$\",\"section\",\"practice\",{\"id\":\"practice\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Practice Recommendations\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"<h2>What to practice next</h2>\\n<ol>\\n<li>Re-solve <strong>Query Kth Smallest Trimmed Number</strong> in a second language (cpp, python).</li>\\n<li>Drill 3–5 more problems tagged <strong>sort</strong>.</li>\\n<li>Teach the solution out loud in under 5 minutes.</li>\\n<li>Add this problem to your revision calendar in 3 days and 14 days.</li>\\n</ol>\\n\"}}]]}]\n16:[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"id\":\"visualization\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold mb-3\",\"children\":\"Visualization\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"rounded-xl border border-dashed border-border bg-muted/40 p-6 text-sm text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"Conceptual diagram for Query Kth Smallest Trimmed Number: show input structure (sort), highlight the moving parts of the sort and radix sort approach, and annotate each step with the maintained invariant and complexity.\"}]]}]\n17:[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"id\":\"checklist\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold mb-3\",\"children\":\"Study checklist\"}],[\"$\",\"ul\",null,{\"className\":\"space-y-2\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"li\",\"Read the official problem statement on LeetCode\",{\"className\":\"flex gap-2 text-sm\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"text-primary\",\"aria-hidden\":true,\"children\":\"☐